						               													<description>H Of Truce is a short, abstract game of tactical tile movement for two players. The object of the game is to capture the enemy's commander with one of your own soldiers. However your opponent is trying to achieve the same goal. And it seems like he's always one step ahead of you. Or is he?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In H Of Truce both players control six soldier pieces who move across an ever changing playing field and try to reach the enemies immobile commander piece via an &amp;quot;action inflation&amp;quot;-mechanic: Both players alternate turns, always taking one action more than their opponent had beforehand, until the game ends or one of the players chooses to reset the action point track back to one action, if he spots a way for his opponent to win with the number of actions he would get. This leads to short, dynamic games with almost no luck, but a lot of clever moves and surprises.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
